      "text": "\"Performative Populism\", a phrase coined by Albert Burneko, describes the sort of populism one sees on Good Morning America, talk radio, and Twitter when some hallowed national or regional tradition is mucked with. Can people say \"Season's Greetings\" instead of Merry Christmas? Are weddings weddings if they toss birdseed instead of rice? Can real Americans put peas in guacamole? Can one eat pizza with a knife and fork? [http://foodspin.deadspin.com/put-peas-in-your-guacamole-if-you-want-to-1715449139 post]"
